WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.754 --> 00:00:07.298
<i>It is time for war.</i>

2
00:00:07.299 --> 00:00:09.634
- Help.
-  <i>Better to stay hidden</i>

3
00:00:09.635 --> 00:00:11.386
<i>and wait for him to recover.</i>

4
00:00:11.387 --> 00:00:13.388
<i>You said
you didn't love my other mom.</i>

5
00:00:13.389 --> 00:00:15.056
My real mom.

6
00:00:15.057 --> 00:00:16.850
That she was a mistake.

7
00:00:16.851 --> 00:00:18.810
Am I a mistake. too?

8
00:00:18.811 --> 00:00:20.520
I'll always find my way back to you.

9
00:00:20.521 --> 00:00:22.856
<i>I'm gonna miss it here.</i>

10
00:00:22.857 --> 00:00:25.191
<i>You were out almost two months.</i>

11
00:00:25.192 --> 00:00:27.819
<i>Thaedus believes
he has won this war.</i>

12
00:00:27.820 --> 00:00:31.197
<i>That he and his allies are safe
on his adopted planet.</i>

13
00:00:35.286 --> 00:00:36.828
<i>Thragg's returning to Viltrum.</i>

14
00:00:36.829 --> 00:00:38.496
<i>He's gonna regroup there.</i>

15
00:00:38.497 --> 00:00:41.666
<i>If we strike Thragg now.
before he's joined</i>

16
00:00:41.667 --> 00:00:43.460
by his remaining forces.

17
00:00:43.461 --> 00:00:47.173
we may have a chance
to end this war forever.

18
00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:55.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

19
00:01:44.522 --> 00:01:47.148
This is the third act of sabotage

20
00:01:47.149 --> 00:01:50.068
by the Relonian natives this week.

21
00:01:50.069 --> 00:01:52.779
The species remains unusually defiant.

22
00:01:52.780 --> 00:01:57.033
despite our clear demonstrations
of Viltrumite superiority.

23
00:01:57.034 --> 00:02:00.495
I recommend
a planet-wide cull of the population

24
00:02:00.496 --> 00:02:04.082
before they disrupt
our mining operations any further.

25
00:02:04.083 --> 00:02:07.001
They resist us because we are occupiers

26
00:02:07.002 --> 00:02:09.712
and we are cruel.

27
00:02:09.713 --> 00:02:12.048
If we restrain ourselves.

28
00:02:12.049 --> 00:02:16.094
their labor will only aid in our goals.

29
00:02:16.095 --> 00:02:19.848
Their labor is nothing
without their fear and respect.

30
00:02:19.849 --> 00:02:21.808
Decimation sets an example.

31
00:02:21.809 --> 00:02:26.145
not only for them.
but for the next misguided species.

32
00:02:26.146 --> 00:02:27.814
Misguided?

33
00:02:27.815 --> 00:02:31.109
Do Viltrumites not respect strength?

34
00:02:31.110 --> 00:02:34.237
The courage
to challenge one's oppressors?

35
00:02:34.238 --> 00:02:37.490
They are nothing to us.

36
00:02:37.491 --> 00:02:39.702
The fact
that you believe otherwise makes me--

37
00:02:43.289 --> 00:02:45.040
Regent Thragg.

38
00:02:46.041 --> 00:02:48.126
Emperor Argall.

39
00:02:48.127 --> 00:02:49.712
What is your counsel?

40
00:02:51.213 --> 00:02:55.216
Thaedus. you say
Viltrumites respect strength.

41
00:02:55.217 --> 00:02:57.302
That is correct. We do.

42
00:02:57.303 --> 00:02:59.804
But these creatures.

43
00:02:59.805 --> 00:03:03.099
their strength is not true strength.

44
00:03:03.100 --> 00:03:07.270
We must educate them
not because of their defiance.

45
00:03:07.271 --> 00:03:11.190
but because their weakness is an offense
to the natural order of the universe.

46
00:03:11.191 --> 00:03:13.026
You are young. Regent.

47
00:03:13.027 --> 00:03:15.778
Perhaps you do not yet
see the longer game--

48
00:03:15.779 --> 00:03:17.615
Regent Thragg is correct.

49
00:03:18.908 --> 00:03:22.286
Reduce the planet's population by 25%.

50
00:03:23.412 --> 00:03:25.455
If they continue to resist.

51
00:03:25.456 --> 00:03:27.082
eradicate them.

52
00:03:28.167 --> 00:03:31.795
Emperor. I urge you to reconsider.

53
00:03:33.964 --> 00:03:35.049
Do you?

54
00:03:43.182 --> 00:03:46.559
<i>Thaedus and I fought
side by side at Capida Minor.</i>

55
00:03:46.560 --> 00:03:49.646
He was the strongest among our company.

56
00:03:49.647 --> 00:03:51.272
the most ruthless.

57
00:03:51.273 --> 00:03:56.027
Yet ever since he returned
from his years in the Lay quadrant.

58
00:03:56.028 --> 00:03:58.279
he speaks of mercy

59
00:03:58.280 --> 00:04:00.907
and questions our ways.

60
00:04:00.908 --> 00:04:02.284
It is troubling.

61
00:04:15.673 --> 00:04:19.926
If you feel his weakness harms the empire.

62
00:04:19.927 --> 00:04:21.929
take action.

63
00:04:24.598 --> 00:04:27.726
Perhaps I am... mistaken.

64
00:05:29.038 --> 00:05:32.457
Emperor Argall showed us our strength.

65
00:05:32.458 --> 00:05:35.418
<i>taught us our greatness.</i>

66
00:05:35.419 --> 00:05:38.504
<i>gave us our destiny.</i>

67
00:05:38.505 --> 00:05:42.885
<i>Because of him. all is ours.</i>

68
00:05:43.677 --> 00:05:46.220
All is ours.

69
00:05:46.221 --> 00:05:49.182
The traitor has fled. but he will be found

70
00:05:49.183 --> 00:05:51.768
and pay the price for his treason.

71
00:05:51.769 --> 00:05:53.437
Be sure of that.

72
00:05:54.772 --> 00:05:58.858
Even in death. Emperor Argall shows us

73
00:05:58.859 --> 00:06:02.987
there is a sickness in our society.

74
00:06:02.988 --> 00:06:05.990
poisoning us from within.

75
00:06:05.991 --> 00:06:10.370
We will cut this cancer out.

76
00:06:11.455 --> 00:06:15.209
You. Might you also betray us someday?

77
00:06:16.043 --> 00:06:18.337
I will not. Grand Regent.

78
00:06:20.339 --> 00:06:22.591
I do not believe you.

79
00:06:38.190 --> 00:06:40.691
As our customs dictate.

80
00:06:40.692 --> 00:06:42.443
I now assume the throne

81
00:06:42.444 --> 00:06:45.071
<i>as Grand Regent of Viltrum
until one of Argall's</i>

82
00:06:45.072 --> 00:06:47.449
<i>heirs can be found.</i>

83
00:06:48.659 --> 00:06:50.953
<i>This is my first command.</i>

84
00:06:52.329 --> 00:06:55.873
Seek out the weakness
that allowed this betrayal...

85
00:06:58.252 --> 00:07:02.464
...and purge it from our midst.

86
00:09:45.210 --> 00:09:47.795
Yes.

87
00:09:47.796 --> 00:09:48.880
No.

88
00:09:53.260 --> 00:09:55.012
It is done.

89
00:10:01.810 --> 00:10:03.770
I will not repeat myself.

90
00:10:09.151 --> 00:10:11.778
Yes. Grand Regent.

91
00:10:15.991 --> 00:10:20.786
<i>The blood
that ran through our streets</i>

92
00:10:20.787 --> 00:10:22.873
<i>has cleansed us.</i>

93
00:10:23.874 --> 00:10:27.752
For you. the strong.

94
00:10:27.753 --> 00:10:30.504
your life is its own reward.

95
00:10:30.505 --> 00:10:33.758
But our work is not yet done.

96
00:10:33.759 --> 00:10:36.385
For even in death.

97
00:10:36.386 --> 00:10:39.264
Argall still guides us.

98
00:10:40.766 --> 00:10:42.183
We will follow his path

99
00:10:42.184 --> 00:10:46.354
<i>and take our place
as the rightful rulers of the galaxy.</i>

100
00:10:46.355 --> 00:10:49.316
<i>The universe itself will kneel.</i>

101
00:10:50.567 --> 00:10:53.152
<i>As it was meant to be.</i>

102
00:10:53.153 --> 00:10:56.323
All is ours.

103
00:10:57.741 --> 00:11:00.618
All is ours!

104
00:11:00.619 --> 00:11:06.624
All is ours! All...

105
00:11:06.625 --> 00:11:08.502
<i>is ours!</i>

106
00:11:21.598 --> 00:11:23.558
I failed you. my emperor.

107
00:11:26.186 --> 00:11:28.146
But I will not fail our people.

108
00:11:29.523 --> 00:11:31.024
Not again.

109
00:11:35.487 --> 00:11:37.947
All our intelligence agrees.

110
00:11:37.948 --> 00:11:42.159
Thragg has retreated to Viltrum
with no more than a few of his people.

111
00:11:42.160 --> 00:11:44.328
The rest are on their way there.

112
00:11:44.329 --> 00:11:46.705
but will not arrive for several days.

113
00:11:46.706 --> 00:11:49.792
This is our chance.

114
00:11:49.793 --> 00:11:53.671
a brief moment
when the regent is vulnerable.

115
00:11:53.672 --> 00:11:56.507
Um. Great Thaedus?

116
00:11:56.508 --> 00:11:59.218
Don't get me wrong.
I would love to kill Thragg

117
00:11:59.219 --> 00:12:01.679
for. like. a million reasons.
But won't that still leave us

118
00:12:01.680 --> 00:12:05.266
with 40-something extra pissed-off
Viltrumites out for revenge?

119
00:12:05.267 --> 00:12:08.602
Since the assassination of Emperor Argall.

120
00:12:08.603 --> 00:12:10.772
they have known no leader but Thragg.

121
00:12:11.815 --> 00:12:15.860
His loss will leave them
weak and directionless.

122
00:12:15.861 --> 00:12:19.489
fighting amongst themselves
as they did before.

123
00:12:20.532 --> 00:12:22.700
It will not be easy.

124
00:12:22.701 --> 00:12:27.372
but once Thragg is gone.
the others will fall one by one.

125
00:12:28.915 --> 00:12:32.460
Alone. Thragg could defeat any one of us.

126
00:12:32.461 --> 00:12:37.673
But together.
we have a chance to end this war forever.

127
00:12:37.674 --> 00:12:39.967
The future of the galaxy

128
00:12:39.968 --> 00:12:42.303
depends on us.

129
00:12:42.304 --> 00:12:45.098
and we may not all return.

130
00:12:46.099 --> 00:12:48.934
But it is worth any price

131
00:12:48.935 --> 00:12:54.064
to show the Viltrum Empire.
once and for all.

132
00:12:54.065 --> 00:12:58.360
that even their strength
does not make them...

133
00:13:05.368 --> 00:13:07.412
<i>We're on our way
to fight this Thragg guy.</i>

134
00:13:08.288 --> 00:13:10.498
Um. it's just him.

135
00:13:10.499 --> 00:13:13.042
plus two or three others.

136
00:13:13.043 --> 00:13:16.670
versus eight of us. so... easy. right?

137
00:13:16.671 --> 00:13:19.798
But apparently.
he was specially trained from birth

138
00:13:19.799 --> 00:13:21.843
to be the strongest Viltrumite ever.

139
00:13:22.969 --> 00:13:25.305
Even my dad's freaking out
about facing him.

140
00:13:26.765 --> 00:13:28.266
Eve. I don't know.

141
00:13:29.392 --> 00:13:31.936
This feels. uh...

142
00:13:31.937 --> 00:13:34.188
this feels different.

143
00:13:34.189 --> 00:13:36.357
And it's my last chance
to record a message for you

144
00:13:36.358 --> 00:13:38.317
just in case something happens.

145
00:13:38.318 --> 00:13:39.778
and. um...

146
00:13:41.780 --> 00:13:43.572
You know what?

147
00:13:43.573 --> 00:13:45.533
You're never even gonna see this because

148
00:13:45.534 --> 00:13:48.036
I love you and I'm coming back.

149
00:13:51.081 --> 00:13:53.165
I cannot believe it. You. too?

150
00:13:53.166 --> 00:13:56.627
I didn't say they were gross.
I said I didn't want one.

151
00:13:56.628 --> 00:13:58.796
Yeah. I know. No one does.

152
00:13:58.797 --> 00:14:00.673
Hey. I'll eat anything.

153
00:14:00.674 --> 00:14:03.634
My dad calls me
the human garbage disposal.

154
00:14:03.635 --> 00:14:07.221
I just never have
much of an appetite when I'm nervous.

155
00:14:07.222 --> 00:14:09.683
Also. those things have faces.

156
00:14:10.684 --> 00:14:12.476
Your moo-cows have faces.

157
00:14:12.477 --> 00:14:16.605
Okay. first. no one older than three
calls them "moo-cows."

158
00:14:16.606 --> 00:14:20.568
And second. they don't have faces
when I eat them.

159
00:14:24.614 --> 00:14:27.783
Why is everyone so nervous
about fighting this Thragg guy?

160
00:14:27.784 --> 00:14:29.660
No way he lives up to the hype.

161
00:14:29.661 --> 00:14:31.704
You haven't seen the reports.

162
00:14:31.705 --> 00:14:33.163
What do they say?

163
00:14:33.164 --> 00:14:34.873
That he lives up to the hype.

164
00:14:34.874 --> 00:14:36.835
We'll see.

165
00:14:39.254 --> 00:14:40.629
You guys are all crazy.

166
00:14:40.630 --> 00:14:41.922
You gotta eat something.

167
00:14:41.923 --> 00:14:44.675
The Unopan is correct.

168
00:14:44.676 --> 00:14:48.262
We must nourish ourselves before battle.

169
00:14:48.263 --> 00:14:52.850
Later. we will feast
on our enemies' entrails.

170
00:14:52.851 --> 00:14:55.312
Or they on ours.

171
00:14:57.022 --> 00:14:59.566
So this might be our last meal. huh?

172
00:15:01.776 --> 00:15:04.320
Fantastic.

173
00:15:04.321 --> 00:15:07.781
If you could eat anything
right now. what would it be?

174
00:15:07.782 --> 00:15:09.700
Burger Mart drive-thru.

175
00:15:09.701 --> 00:15:13.037
Boom. Triple triple. Yes.

176
00:15:13.038 --> 00:15:15.873
Ooh. with loaded fries
from the secret menu.

177
00:15:15.874 --> 00:15:17.958
It's my thing with my dad.

178
00:15:17.959 --> 00:15:21.128
Actually. if I really had to pick.

179
00:15:21.129 --> 00:15:24.048
Paul's spaghetti.
He's my mom's boyfriend.

180
00:15:24.049 --> 00:15:26.134
He makes his own meatballs
and everything.

181
00:15:27.052 --> 00:15:30.055
Mm. The Brain Bowl at the Galactic Grill.

182
00:15:31.931 --> 00:15:34.266
I am already eating it.

183
00:15:34.267 --> 00:15:37.519
My final meal will be my own blood.

184
00:15:37.520 --> 00:15:41.315
as I choke on it. breathing my last breath

185
00:15:41.316 --> 00:15:45.069
after a legendary battle
with a superior opponent.

186
00:15:46.404 --> 00:15:49.658
That will be a satisfying meal indeed.

187
00:15:56.831 --> 00:15:58.248
Mmm!

188
00:15:58.249 --> 00:15:59.751
Right?

189
00:16:01.753 --> 00:16:03.796
You seem worried. Nolan.

190
00:16:03.797 --> 00:16:05.507
I am.

191
00:16:06.841 --> 00:16:09.051
You should be. too.

192
00:16:09.052 --> 00:16:12.096
This is the best chance
we've had in centuries

193
00:16:12.097 --> 00:16:13.806
to end this conflict.

194
00:16:13.807 --> 00:16:16.434
But that is not what troubles you.

195
00:16:17.769 --> 00:16:19.228
No.

196
00:16:19.229 --> 00:16:21.397
Thragg must die.

197
00:16:21.398 --> 00:16:23.524
But the other Viltrumites...

198
00:16:23.525 --> 00:16:25.025
You said it yourself.

199
00:16:25.026 --> 00:16:27.861
they'll be weak and scattered
without him.

200
00:16:27.862 --> 00:16:31.700
And yet. still capable
of untold death and destruction.

201
00:16:32.909 --> 00:16:35.869
I will not risk even the smallest chance

202
00:16:35.870 --> 00:16:38.206
their empire could rise again.

203
00:16:40.709 --> 00:16:44.713
Mark and Oliver are part Viltrumite. too.

204
00:16:45.964 --> 00:16:49.133
<i>Everyone. we've reached
Viltrum's sensor range.</i>

205
00:16:49.134 --> 00:16:50.927
<i>Time to get ready.</i>

206
00:16:56.683 --> 00:16:58.475
We've only got ten of these?

207
00:16:58.476 --> 00:17:00.769
You have no idea
how difficult that sinlak poison

208
00:17:00.770 --> 00:17:03.272
was to extract and refine.

209
00:17:03.273 --> 00:17:05.817
Ah. Soon.

210
00:17:13.616 --> 00:17:15.243
Thaedus is coming too?

211
00:17:16.453 --> 00:17:17.746
He's. like. a million years...

212
00:17:18.913 --> 00:17:20.247
...old.

213
00:17:20.248 --> 00:17:21.790
Never mind.

214
00:17:21.791 --> 00:17:23.208
Listen to me.

215
00:17:23.209 --> 00:17:25.210
However strong you think you are.

216
00:17:25.211 --> 00:17:27.921
Thragg is stronger.

217
00:17:27.922 --> 00:17:30.174
Don't let him draw you
away from the group.

218
00:17:30.175 --> 00:17:33.635
That also means you don't
try to take him on alone. Oliver.

219
00:17:33.636 --> 00:17:34.887
I won't.

220
00:17:34.888 --> 00:17:36.722
We stick together.

221
00:17:36.723 --> 00:17:38.349
That's how we win this.

222
00:17:39.476 --> 00:17:41.977
If anything happens.

223
00:17:41.978 --> 00:17:43.687
just remember I...

224
00:17:45.273 --> 00:17:46.983
Ah...

225
00:17:48.485 --> 00:17:49.903
We know.

226
00:17:58.995 --> 00:18:01.498
I am gonna be so bummed
if I don't survive this.

227
00:18:04.167 --> 00:18:06.126
Is everyone ready?

228
00:18:06.127 --> 00:18:08.629
Stick to the plan.

229
00:18:08.630 --> 00:18:10.798
Sneak in past their sensors.

230
00:18:10.799 --> 00:18:13.593
then scour the planet
as quickly as possible.

231
00:18:14.594 --> 00:18:18.055
You all have coordinates
for the regent's most likely locations.

232
00:18:18.056 --> 00:18:20.057
When you find him.

233
00:18:20.058 --> 00:18:22.309
call in everyone else.

234
00:18:22.310 --> 00:18:25.646
Remember. Thragg's death

235
00:18:25.647 --> 00:18:27.773
is the only thing that matters.

236
00:18:44.082 --> 00:18:46.124
What are you waiting for?

237
00:18:49.003 --> 00:18:51.297
Go save the galaxy already.

238
00:18:59.389 --> 00:19:02.516
<i>Whoa. Are those...</i>

239
00:19:02.517 --> 00:19:03.684
<i>Yes.</i>

240
00:19:03.685 --> 00:19:08.355
<i>After Emperor Argall's assassination
and the Purge.</i>

241
00:19:08.356 --> 00:19:11.441
<i>our empire expanded rapidly
as we conquered planets</i>

242
00:19:11.442 --> 00:19:14.361
<i>in memory of the leader we lost.</i>

243
00:19:14.362 --> 00:19:18.907
<i>But it wasn't long
before the scourge virus came</i>

244
00:19:18.908 --> 00:19:20.785
<i>and took almost all of us.</i>

245
00:19:22.704 --> 00:19:25.665
<i>This was the most fitting tomb
we could think of.</i>

246
00:19:26.958 --> 00:19:29.334
<i>Every time we left our home.</i>

247
00:19:29.335 --> 00:19:32.462
<i>we'd be reminded of our weakness</i>

248
00:19:32.463 --> 00:19:34.256
<i>and failure.</i>

249
00:19:34.257 --> 00:19:37.134
<i>They will help
conceal our approach.</i>

250
00:20:00.158 --> 00:20:02.868
<i>Uh... guys?</i>

251
00:20:14.505 --> 00:20:16.840
<i>Well. at least now
we don't need to waste a lot of time</i>

252
00:20:16.841 --> 00:20:18.676
<i>looking for him. right? Heh.</i>

253
00:20:20.428 --> 00:20:22.596
<i>This changes nothing.</i>

254
00:20:31.856 --> 00:20:33.483
<i>They knew we were coming.</i>

255
00:20:34.943 --> 00:20:37.736
<i>It doesn't matter. Kill Thragg!</i>

256
00:20:37.737 --> 00:20:39.656
<i>Yes!</i>

257
00:21:08.017 --> 00:21:08.935
<i>Traitor!</i>

258
00:21:12.397 --> 00:21:14.231
<i>You dare return here--</i>

259
00:21:16.317 --> 00:21:18.444
<i>This bug juice better work!</i>

260
00:21:20.029 --> 00:21:21.197
<i>Huh?</i>

261
00:21:23.783 --> 00:21:25.827
<i>Eat shit!</i>

262
00:21:27.745 --> 00:21:30.831
<i>Okay. it works!
It definitely works!</i>

263
00:21:30.832 --> 00:21:32.834
<i>Great! Shoot someone else!</i>

264
00:21:41.467 --> 00:21:44.345
<i>I should have killed you both
on Thraxa!</i>

265
00:21:49.559 --> 00:21:51.269
<i>The betrayer!</i>

266
00:21:58.151 --> 00:22:00.944
<i>You were always weak. Kregg.</i>

267
00:22:08.119 --> 00:22:09.287
<i>Oliver!</i>

268
00:22:15.668 --> 00:22:17.795
<i>So disappointing.</i>

269
00:22:34.145 --> 00:22:37.065
<i>Your time on Earth has
made you soft.</i>

270
00:22:38.149 --> 00:22:39.233
<i>Don't count on it.</i>

271
00:22:47.283 --> 00:22:48.367
More!

272
00:22:49.494 --> 00:22:50.661
More!

273
00:23:06.552 --> 00:23:09.180
<i>Allen! Get to Thaedus!</i>

274
00:23:11.140 --> 00:23:14.226
<i>What? Oh. shit. On my way!</i>

275
00:23:45.508 --> 00:23:48.051
<i>Kill him before he fires again!</i>

276
00:23:48.052 --> 00:23:51.847
It's not my gun
you should be worried about.

277
00:23:54.225 --> 00:23:55.725
<i>Now!</i>

278
00:24:14.245 --> 00:24:15.246
<i>Allen!</i>

279
00:24:20.626 --> 00:24:21.710
<i>Save the darts!</i>

280
00:24:25.089 --> 00:24:27.758
<i>These things are doing
just fine on their own.</i>

281
00:24:43.524 --> 00:24:44.525
<i>Go!</i>

282
00:25:37.286 --> 00:25:39.789
It's been too long. Nolan.

283
00:25:47.463 --> 00:25:49.006
What do you want. Thragg?

284
00:25:50.091 --> 00:25:52.926
Simply to talk to an old friend.

285
00:25:52.927 --> 00:25:54.679
Since when do we talk?

286
00:25:55.763 --> 00:25:57.348
We've always talked.

287
00:25:58.224 --> 00:26:00.518
Some simply chose not to listen.

288
00:26:01.602 --> 00:26:02.979
Then talk.

289
00:26:06.732 --> 00:26:08.025
Come home. Nolan.

290
00:26:09.277 --> 00:26:12.028
Come home and all will be forgiven.

291
00:26:14.532 --> 00:26:15.783
We have no home.

292
00:26:17.451 --> 00:26:19.452
This place is a tomb.

293
00:26:19.453 --> 00:26:21.747
Viltrum is not a tomb!

294
00:26:23.916 --> 00:26:25.167
Mm.

295
00:26:28.296 --> 00:26:30.547
It is who we are.

296
00:26:32.383 --> 00:26:35.010
We will restore it to what it was.

297
00:26:35.011 --> 00:26:37.887
as we will restore our people
to their rightful place

298
00:26:37.888 --> 00:26:39.889
in the galaxy.

299
00:26:39.890 --> 00:26:42.476
There's barely 40 of us left. Thragg.

300
00:26:44.520 --> 00:26:49.733
Forty Viltrumites who know you
better than you know yourself.

301
00:26:49.734 --> 00:26:51.443
Who have fought beside you.

302
00:26:51.444 --> 00:26:54.405
Who have suffered
exactly the same way you have.

303
00:26:56.324 --> 00:26:58.326
You're not my family anymore.

304
00:26:59.201 --> 00:27:03.663
But the man
who almost caused our extinction is?

305
00:27:03.664 --> 00:27:07.500
I know Thaedus created
the scourge virus.

306
00:27:07.501 --> 00:27:09.503
And yet. you fight beside him.

307
00:27:10.796 --> 00:27:14.257
He committed genocide on his own people.

308
00:27:14.258 --> 00:27:17.677
To stop us from committing it on others.

309
00:27:17.678 --> 00:27:21.681
You know we only ever did
what was necessary to preserve order.

310
00:27:21.682 --> 00:27:23.726
Like coming after my sons?

311
00:27:25.186 --> 00:27:28.230
We tested your sons.
as we have all been tested.

312
00:27:29.398 --> 00:27:33.194
Do you think Thaedus will be
as kind to them if he wins this war?

313
00:27:38.616 --> 00:27:40.200
Ah.

314
00:27:40.201 --> 00:27:43.204
I see you're not as naive as I feared.

315
00:28:06.685 --> 00:28:09.145
<i>Ridiculous creatures.</i>

316
00:28:09.146 --> 00:28:11.564
<i>A distraction at best.</i>

317
00:28:11.565 --> 00:28:16.027
<i>That is what you think
of every species but your own. Lucan.</i>

318
00:28:16.028 --> 00:28:18.531
<i>You'll soon learn better.</i>

319
00:28:57.486 --> 00:28:58.570
<i>Hold on.</i>

320
00:28:58.571 --> 00:29:01.031
<i>Repairing exterior object.</i>

321
00:29:05.703 --> 00:29:07.912
Thank... thank you.

322
00:29:07.913 --> 00:29:10.206
<i>It's all good.
Just keep kicking ass.</i>

323
00:29:17.256 --> 00:29:21.010
This room once echoed
with thousands of voices.

324
00:29:22.470 --> 00:29:27.349
All united with the knowledge
that the universe belonged to Viltrum.

325
00:29:28.350 --> 00:29:30.977
Argall showed us this.

326
00:29:30.978 --> 00:29:33.731
Taught us our true power.

327
00:29:34.899 --> 00:29:36.941
Thaedus...

328
00:29:36.942 --> 00:29:39.486
Thaedus was a coward.

329
00:29:39.487 --> 00:29:41.696
You know that. don't you?

330
00:29:41.697 --> 00:29:43.865
It doesn't change anything.

331
00:29:43.866 --> 00:29:48.203
Fighting for him is
fighting for your own destruction.

332
00:29:48.204 --> 00:29:50.872
Your family's destruction.

333
00:29:50.873 --> 00:29:53.375
I won't let him hurt my family.

334
00:29:54.460 --> 00:29:56.086
You already have.

335
00:29:57.588 --> 00:29:59.714
It's over. Thragg.

336
00:29:59.715 --> 00:30:03.635
The entire galaxy is unified against us.

337
00:30:03.636 --> 00:30:06.221
But it doesn't have to end
with our extinction.

338
00:30:06.222 --> 00:30:09.599
Agree to terms and I will stop this.

339
00:30:09.600 --> 00:30:12.310
no matter what Thaedus wants.

340
00:30:12.311 --> 00:30:15.939
Would our emperor ever agree to terms?

341
00:30:15.940 --> 00:30:19.067
Look around. Thragg.

342
00:30:19.068 --> 00:30:21.069
We lost.

343
00:30:21.070 --> 00:30:23.446
Can't you see why all this fell?

344
00:30:23.447 --> 00:30:26.491
This is our home.

345
00:30:26.492 --> 00:30:28.577
We will rebuild it.

346
00:30:31.121 --> 00:30:32.289
No.

347
00:30:33.374 --> 00:30:35.125
You won't.

348
00:30:38.504 --> 00:30:42.925
The death of any Viltrumite
leaves a void in me.

349
00:30:46.762 --> 00:30:48.597
Uh...

350
00:31:17.501 --> 00:31:19.210
<i>Hey. dickhead!</i>

351
00:31:19.211 --> 00:31:20.546
<i>A black hole called.</i>

352
00:31:22.381 --> 00:31:23.716
<i>It wants its suck back!</i>

353
00:31:26.093 --> 00:31:28.095
<i>You are not one of us.</i>

354
00:31:34.560 --> 00:31:35.560
<i>Oliver!</i>

355
00:31:39.148 --> 00:31:40.524
<i>No!</i>

356
00:31:45.529 --> 00:31:47.572
<i>The child was a failure.</i>

357
00:31:47.573 --> 00:31:49.657
<i>He was no brother to you.</i>

358
00:31:49.658 --> 00:31:51.951
<i>I killed Conquest.</i>

359
00:31:51.952 --> 00:31:53.579
<i>I'll kill you. too.</i>

360
00:31:59.084 --> 00:32:01.003
<i>Show me.</i>

361
00:32:16.226 --> 00:32:18.729
<i>I'm not impressed.</i>

362
00:32:48.384 --> 00:32:49.802
<i>Zoe!</i>

363
00:32:50.719 --> 00:32:51.804
<i>Quick!</i>

364
00:32:55.182 --> 00:32:56.599
<i>Ammunition depleted.</i>

365
00:32:56.600 --> 00:32:58.852
<i>Oh. shit. I'm out.</i>

366
00:33:17.329 --> 00:33:19.330
<i>Kill me if you can.</i>

367
00:33:19.331 --> 00:33:21.916
<i>and die if you cannot.</i>

368
00:33:21.917 --> 00:33:24.335
<i>so I may find a better foe.</i>

369
00:33:24.336 --> 00:33:25.420
<i>Animal.</i>

370
00:33:44.648 --> 00:33:45.773
<i>Finally!</i>

371
00:33:45.774 --> 00:33:47.651
<i>No.</i>

372
00:33:58.704 --> 00:34:01.456
<i>Everyone with me. Now.</i>

373
00:34:20.726 --> 00:34:23.060
<i>Forget him. I need you.</i>

374
00:34:23.061 --> 00:34:25.104
<i>What are we doing?</i>

375
00:34:25.105 --> 00:34:26.857
<i>Space Racer. out front.</i>

376
00:34:36.450 --> 00:34:39.286
<i>No! Stay with me.</i>

377
00:34:44.166 --> 00:34:45.542
<i>No.</i>

378
00:34:46.627 --> 00:34:48.211
<i>No way. We can't.</i>

379
00:34:48.212 --> 00:34:50.380
<i>Mark. Trust me.</i>

380
00:34:51.381 --> 00:34:53.299
<i>Space Racer.</i>

381
00:34:53.300 --> 00:34:54.510
<i>Now!</i>

382
00:34:56.720 --> 00:34:58.096
<i>No.</i>

383
00:34:59.097 --> 00:35:00.348
<i>No!</i>

384
00:35:29.753 --> 00:35:31.171
Keep close.

385
00:35:32.297 --> 00:35:33.840
Hold together!

386
00:36:13.297 --> 00:36:14.631
<i>Whoa.</i>

387
00:40:08.073 --> 00:40:09.240
<i>Zoe!</i>

388
00:40:32.848 --> 00:40:36.810
<i>It was the only way
to show them the truth.</i>

389
00:40:38.687 --> 00:40:40.147
<i>I know.</i>

390
00:40:42.149 --> 00:40:44.233
<i>Oliver. Where's Oliver?</i>

391
00:41:05.547 --> 00:41:07.590
<i>Viltrumites!</i>

392
00:41:07.591 --> 00:41:12.011
<i>Your world is destroyed.</i>

393
00:41:12.012 --> 00:41:16.724
<i>Surrender is your only option.</i>

394
00:41:16.725 --> 00:41:18.685
<i>No!</i>

395
00:41:23.648 --> 00:41:26.902
<i>I choose death!</i>

396
00:41:36.745 --> 00:41:41.958
<i>Emperor Argall. you are avenged.</i>

397
00:41:47.881 --> 00:41:51.383
<i>You are all next.</i>

398
00:41:57.140 --> 00:41:59.850
<i>Thaedus. Oh. God.</i>

399
00:41:59.851 --> 00:42:01.310
<i>Allen.</i>

400
00:42:01.311 --> 00:42:02.729
<i>Find Oliver.</i>

401
00:42:04.064 --> 00:42:05.397
<i>Allen!</i>

402
00:42:05.398 --> 00:42:08.068
<i>Yeah. Yeah. o-okay.</i>

403
00:42:13.657 --> 00:42:16.158
<i>I offered you forgiveness.</i>

404
00:42:16.159 --> 00:42:20.997
<i>I offered you an honorable death.</i>

405
00:42:23.667 --> 00:42:25.376
<i>Instead.</i>

406
00:42:25.377 --> 00:42:28.838
<i>you destroyed everything.</i>

407
00:42:48.858 --> 00:42:51.151
<i>I was too quick with Thaedus.</i>

408
00:42:51.152 --> 00:42:54.406
<i>I won't make the same mistake with you.</i>

409
00:42:58.994 --> 00:43:01.954
<i>Okay. I understand
you are all a little surprised</i>

410
00:43:01.955 --> 00:43:04.457
<i>and upset about what just happened.</i>

411
00:43:06.501 --> 00:43:08.335
<i>Uh. Space Racer?</i>

412
00:43:08.336 --> 00:43:10.171
<i>Space Racer!</i>

413
00:43:51.171 --> 00:43:52.797
<i>Allen!</i>

414
00:43:56.343 --> 00:43:58.260
-  <i>Zoe!</i>
-  <i>It's okay.</i>

415
00:43:58.261 --> 00:43:59.929
<i>I got him.</i>

416
00:44:02.724 --> 00:44:04.433
We have to go.

417
00:44:04.434 --> 00:44:06.769
<i>We can't leave Mark and Nolan.</i>

418
00:44:06.770 --> 00:44:08.020
<i>And where's Oliver?</i>

419
00:44:08.021 --> 00:44:09.481
We can't help them.

420
00:44:47.894 --> 00:44:49.396
<i>You could have been
a Viltrumite...</i>

421
00:44:50.772 --> 00:44:53.400
<i>...but you chose to be noth--</i>

422
00:44:55.527 --> 00:44:58.237
<i>How... how do we beat him?</i>

423
00:44:58.238 --> 00:45:00.697
<i>Mark...</i>

424
00:45:21.636 --> 00:45:23.054
<i>Dad!</i>

425
00:45:26.224 --> 00:45:27.767
<i>What a waste.</i>

426
00:46:18.735 --> 00:46:22.404
<i>Grand Regent. kill him.</i>

427
00:46:22.405 --> 00:46:25.699
<i>They destroyed our home.</i>

428
00:46:25.700 --> 00:46:27.911
<i>Silence.</i>

429
00:46:32.624 --> 00:46:36.001
<i>We are too few already.</i>

430
00:46:45.428 --> 00:46:49.682
<i>What are your orders.
Grand Regent?</i>

431
00:48:17.604 --> 00:48:18.895
Hey.

432
00:48:18.896 --> 00:48:21.231
Hey. buddy. Mark?

433
00:48:21.232 --> 00:48:22.567
You awake?

434
00:48:23.568 --> 00:48:24.901
You are.

435
00:48:24.902 --> 00:48:26.987
Look at that. Welcome back.

436
00:48:29.073 --> 00:48:31.533
Allen. How long...

437
00:48:31.534 --> 00:48:35.078
Couple weeks.
It was touch and go for a while.

438
00:48:35.079 --> 00:48:37.623
Tell you. you guys sure know
how to stress a Unopan out.

439
00:48:42.670 --> 00:48:45.757
Where's Oliver? Where's my dad?

440
00:48:58.227 --> 00:48:59.437
Dad.

441
00:49:06.486 --> 00:49:07.736
You're alive.

442
00:49:07.737 --> 00:49:09.863
Woke up yesterday.

443
00:49:09.864 --> 00:49:11.032
Oliver.

444
00:49:12.116 --> 00:49:14.117
He'll be okay.

445
00:49:14.118 --> 00:49:16.620
He just needs time to heal.

446
00:49:16.621 --> 00:49:18.997
What happened to Thragg and the others?

447
00:49:18.998 --> 00:49:21.668
What's the last thing
you remember?

448
00:49:22.669 --> 00:49:24.461
Thragg had me.

449
00:49:24.462 --> 00:49:26.547
You were... I-I thought you were dead.

450
00:49:27.548 --> 00:49:29.050
Why'd he let us live?

451
00:49:30.051 --> 00:49:32.135
Good question.

452
00:49:32.136 --> 00:49:33.970
But we've got a bigger one.

453
00:49:33.971 --> 00:49:36.973
What? Where are they?

454
00:49:36.974 --> 00:49:39.268
That is the thing.

455
00:49:41.062 --> 00:49:43.188
As all of you know...

456
00:49:45.400 --> 00:49:48.361
Um. as all of you know. Thaedus is dead.

457
00:49:50.321 --> 00:49:53.573
So the council asked someone to lead

458
00:49:53.574 --> 00:49:56.785
until there's time
to appoint his replacement.

459
00:49:56.786 --> 00:50:00.914
And. well. believe it or not.
it's this guy.

460
00:50:00.915 --> 00:50:03.458
They mostly want me to deal
with one small problem.

461
00:50:03.459 --> 00:50:05.419
The remaining Viltrumites.

462
00:50:05.420 --> 00:50:08.130
Yep. General Telia?

463
00:50:08.131 --> 00:50:13.969
We have ships searching sector by sector.
but so far. they've just disappeared.

464
00:50:13.970 --> 00:50:16.680
It's freaking everyone out.

465
00:50:16.681 --> 00:50:19.766
I mean.
the hiding is a good sign. right?

466
00:50:19.767 --> 00:50:23.520
It's not generally
what Viltrumites like to. uh...

467
00:50:23.521 --> 00:50:25.440
Uh. Mark? What's up?

468
00:50:28.443 --> 00:50:30.319
They've gone to Earth.

469
00:50:31.305 --> 00:51:31.515
